Password Generator (Python):
This is a simple Python program that generates a random password based on user preferences.
Features:
Generate secure random passwords
Choose password length
Option to include:
Letters (A–Z, a–z)
Numbers (0–9)
Symbols (!@#$...)
Requirements:
No extra libraries needed 
Uses built-in Python modules:
random
string
How to Run:
Save the file as password.py
Open terminal
Run
Example:
Enter password length: 8
Include letters? (y/n): y
Include numbers? (y/n): y
Include symbols? (y/n): n
Generated Password: aB3kL9xQ
Note:
You must select at least one option (letters, numbers, or symbols)
Otherwise, the program will show an error
Future Improvements:
Add GUI version
Copy password to clipboard 
Save passwords securely 
Password strength checker 
